Learning Outcome: Identify data science applications in human societies

Computational thinking, data science, math, all words that strike fear and perhaps hatred in our hearts and mind. I know I've thought only really smart people can do this and I'm not really smart. Turns out, it's a stereotype and not a very good one. Did you know, dogs do calculus all the time? They use it to play fetch and catch balls.

So how do you data science and computational thinking in your everyday life now that you know more about what these ways of thinking are in relation to others ways of thinking?

Your post should be around 6-8 sentences long with a clear topic sentence at the beginning of each paragraph.

Please add citations of lecture material (or outside sources) to add a broader expertise and knowledge base to your argument.

